---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Overview">
  <h1>Navigato Design System</h1>
  <p class="nvg-lead">
    A React component library for travel booking, trip planning, and short-term rental products —
    built for engineers who need consistent UI patterns across search, map, and booking flows.
  </p>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4">
    <h2>What is Navigato?</h2>
    <p>
      Navigato started as an internal Middleman styleguide for a travel product team. This revival
      packages the same design language as <code>@navigato/react</code> — an MIT-licensed npm package
      with live documentation.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
      <li>shadcn/ui primitives + booking composites on Tailwind CSS v4</li>
      <li>Date range pickers, guest selectors, listing cards, booking widgets, price breakdowns</li>
      <li>Accessible Radix/Base UI patterns with keyboard support</li>
      <li>Live demos, copy-paste usage, and props API tables for every component</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2>Explore components</h2>
    <p>
      Browse the library by Atomic Design tier — atoms, molecules, organisms, and demoable pages.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4">
      <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}components/`} class="text-brand font-bold no-underline hover:underline">
        View all components →
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2>Quick install</h2>
    <pre><code>{`npm install @navigato/react

import '@navigato/react/styles.css'
import { BookingSearchBar, ListingCard } from '@navigato/react'`}</code></pre>
    <p class="mt-4">
      <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}getting-started/`} class="text-brand font-bold no-underline hover:underline">
        Read the getting started guide →
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
